header.gameNote: CONTINENTAL TIRE LAS VEGAS CLASSIC AT LAS VEGAS

article.headline: Bethune-Cookman 61, Texas A&amp,M-CC 52
article.story: LAS VEGAS -- Adrian Coleman had 16 points and nine rebounds to lead Bethune-Cookman past Texas A&M-Corpus Christi 61-52 on Thursday in the Las Vegas Classic. Also for the Wildcats (4-9), Anthony Breeze and Kevin Dukes each had nine points. Bethune-Cookman ended a four-game losing streak. Chris Hawkins-Mast led the Islanders (1-9) with 15 points and eight rebounds. James King added 10 points as Texas A&M-Corpus Christi lost its seventh straight. After the Islanders led for most of the first half, Bethune-Cookman went on an 18-4 run starting late in the half and continuing after intermission. The Wildcats took the lead for good by halftime, when they led 30-28. Bethune-Cookman's lead grew to 14 points in the second half.
